#. [unit]: type=Ogre, id=Rek Iceheart
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:109
msgid "Rek Iceheart"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:131
msgid "Ugh... Am I still breathing? My body still aches..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:135
msgid "Gwiti gradually accepted that he had reached some strange beach. The area was quiet but the beastly smell had stayed."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:152
msgid "My shackles are broken. I think, disgustingly, I know that the contrivance of destiny is always ironic... Yet why is there no Nati by my side? Where has he gone?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Xabrak
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:175
msgid "Hey! Look over there! A feeble necromancer is approaching us! But strange... I thought all the cults in this land were vanquished by us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Grakarat
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:179
msgid "I hate humans! I hate skeletons! But I love the feel of crushing their bones."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:201
msgid "... Now it seems I must abandon any consideration and survive from their aggression. Fortunately or unfortunately, there are many bodies left among the ruin that I may evoke. But after I summon them, the time I have left may not be so long."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:212
msgid "Our plunder ends... by the darkness..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:222
msgid "Who is hidden there? I wish you are on my side, though."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Arkal-Thil, type=Dark Adept
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:228
msgid "Arkal-Thil"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:247
msgid "I almost got murdered by them..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:252
msgid "Who the hell are you? My guess is that you are the necromancer... right?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:257
msgid "Exactly. I am the same kind of person as you. I was one of the followers of the darkness who trained in this land. But those beasts came and slayed our master, and destroyed many of us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:261
msgid "So, you want your new master? Then you should join my... uprising."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:265
msgid "Uprising? For what?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:269
msgid "It would be easier to understand if I say that it is revenge against all the corrupt living? You and other survivors of yours have all been oppressed by the mighty... right? I need that kind of anger, that kind of grief."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:273
msgid "It is quite an interesting irony that you remind me of our past. No? In any case, there is no reason to refuse. We will follow you. But in fact, there must be another one who is being held hostage by the ogre."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:288
msgid "Death of Arkal-Thil"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:312
msgid "Argh! I was vanquished!"
msgstr ""

